---
import MainLayout from "../components/MainLayout.astro";

const canonicalPath = "/advisory";
const title = "Advisory";
const summary = "Retained or project-based decision support for automation, robotics, and industrial AI markets.";
---

<MainLayout canonicalPath={canonicalPath} title={title} summary={summary} seoTitle="Advisory | Autonomy Bridge">
  <article class="adv-page">

    <!-- HEADER -->
    <header class="adv-header">
      <div class="adv-container">
        <h1 class="adv-h1">Advisory</h1>
        <p class="adv-tagline">Engagement for AI, Robotics, and Industrial Automation Markets</p>
        <p class="adv-intro">Most consultants arrive with a methodology and map your problem to it. Autonomy Bridge works the other way: the engagement starts with a diagnostic of where your commercial or analytical constraint actually sits, and builds outward from there. The work draws on primary market research, proprietary frameworks across vendor economics, automation ROI, and workflow architecture, and direct operational experience across warehouse, manufacturing, and industrial automation deployments. Engagements are scoped to produce decisions, not decks.</p>
        <div class="adv-header-links">
          <a href="/case-studies">Case Studies →</a>
          <a href="/bespoke-research">Bespoke Research →</a>
          <a href="/methodology">Methodology →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- WHO THIS IS FOR -->
    <section class="adv-section">
      <div class="adv-container">
        <h2 class="adv-h2">Who This Is For</h2>
        <div class="adv-client-grid">
          <div class="adv-client-card">
            <h3 class="adv-client-name">Warehouse &amp; 3PL Operators</h3>
            <p>You are evaluating automation vendors or managing a pilot that hasn't converted to full deployment. The constraint is usually not technology — it's the absence of an economic model that accounts for your actual throughput variability, labor mix, and lease structure. We build that model and translate it into vendor selection criteria or deployment sequencing.</p>
            <a href="/glossary/capital-recovery-period" class="adv-ref-link">Capital Recovery Period →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="adv-client-card">
            <h3 class="adv-client-name">Manufacturing &amp; Industrial Operators</h3>
            <p>You are evaluating robotics or automation for a production environment — assembly, fabrication, materials handling, or end-of-line operations. The economics of industrial deployment differ from warehouse in meaningful ways: cycle time variability, OEM integration complexity, and shift-based utilization patterns require a different analytical model. We build that model and translate it into deployment sequencing, vendor evaluation criteria, or capital recovery analysis.</p>
            <a href="/glossary/automation-roi" class="adv-ref-link">Automation ROI →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="adv-client-card">
            <h3 class="adv-client-name">Logistics &amp; Industrial Automation Investors</h3>
            <p>You are conducting due diligence on a robotics vendor, an autonomous systems company, or a distribution infrastructure asset. You need a market-grounded view of unit economics, competitive positioning, and the realistic path to scaled deployment. We run the research and stress-test the assumptions in the materials you've been given.</p>
            <a href="/glossary/vendor-economics" class="adv-ref-link">Vendor Economics →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="adv-client-card">
            <h3 class="adv-client-name">Robotics &amp; Automation Vendors</h3>
            <p>You are entering a new vertical or segment and lack the buyer-side operational context to position effectively. Your sales cycle is longer than it should be because your team is selling capability, not quantified outcomes. We diagnose the positioning gap and produce the market and buyer intelligence needed to close it.</p>
            <a href="/glossary/workflow-constraint" class="adv-ref-link">Workflow Constraint →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW WE WORK -->
    <section class="adv-section adv-section--surface">
      <div class="adv-container">
        <h2 class="adv-h2">How We Work</h2>
        <div class="adv-models-grid">
          <div class="adv-model">
            <span class="adv-model-label">Retainer</span>
            <p>Standing access to research, iterative output across a defined scope, and a consistent analytical perspective on commercial decisions as they develop. This model works best when you have ongoing decisions to make — vendor evaluation cycles, market entry planning, or sustained sales and pricing strategy work.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="adv-model">
            <span class="adv-model-label">Project-Based</span>
            <p>Scoped to a defined output: a market sizing model, a vendor economics analysis, a workflow constraint diagnostic, or a competitive intelligence report. Timeline and deliverables are fixed at the outset. Appropriate when you have a specific decision to support and a clear analytical gap to fill.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="adv-model-note">Retainer and project engagements can be combined. A project-based diagnostic often reveals a broader set of strategic questions; a retainer can follow from that foundation. Scope is always defined in writing before any work begins.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TYPICAL ENGAGEMENT SCOPE -->
    <section class="adv-section">
      <div class="adv-container">
        <h2 class="adv-h2">Typical Engagement Scope</h2>
        <ul class="adv-scope-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Automation utilization modeling</strong> — capacity and throughput analysis under variable demand, mapped against automation system specifications and labor substitution economics
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Vendor economics analysis</strong> — total cost of ownership across competing automation platforms, normalized for deployment environment, integration complexity, and maintenance burden
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Workflow constraint mapping</strong> — identification of operational bottlenecks limiting automation ROI, with quantified impact on throughput, labor cost, and order cycle time
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Market entry and segment sizing</strong> — addressable market analysis for a specific automation technology or deployment segment, with buyer profile segmentation and competitive positioning assessment
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Commercial diagnostic for robotics vendors</strong> — audit of sales cycle performance, win/loss patterns, and positioning gaps, with go-to-market recommendations grounded in buyer-side operational context
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT WE DON'T DO -->
    <section class="adv-section adv-section--surface">
      <div class="adv-container">
        <h2 class="adv-h2">What We Don't Do</h2>
        <ul class="adv-dont-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Implementation.</strong> We provide analysis, frameworks, and commercial strategy. We do not manage deployments, build software, or staff embedded operations roles.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>General management consulting.</strong> We work in a defined domain: AI, robotics, and industrial automation markets. Engagements outside that domain are declined.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Speculative retainers.</strong> We don't take open-ended engagements without a defined scope. If there isn't a clear analytical or commercial constraint to work on, the timing isn't right.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- START A CONVERSATION -->
    <section class="adv-cta-section">
      <div class="adv-container adv-cta-inner">
        <div>
          <h2 class="adv-cta-heading">Start a Conversation</h2>
          <p class="adv-cta-sub">If you have a specific constraint and want to know whether we can help, describe it directly. Every engagement starts with a 15-minute scoping call — no commitment required.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="adv-cta-actions">
          <a href="/contact" class="adv-btn-primary">Book 15-min scoping call</a>
          <a href="/case-studies" class="adv-btn-outline">See Case Studies</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .adv-page {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
  }

  .adv-container {
    max-width: 56rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* ── HEADER ── */
  .adv-header {
    padding: 3.5rem 0 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
  }

  .adv-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 1.6rem + 1.5vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .adv-tagline {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .adv-intro {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    text-align: justify;
  }

  .adv-header-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .adv-header-links a {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-accent);
    padding-bottom: 0.1rem;
  }

  .adv-header-links a:hover {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* ── SECTIONS ── */
  .adv-section {
    padding: 3.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-light);
  }

  .adv-section--surface {
    background: var(--color-bg-surface);
  }

  .adv-h2 {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  /* ── CLIENT CARDS ── */
  .adv-client-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .adv-client-card {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    border-top: 3px solid var(--color-border-accent);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .adv-client-name {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .adv-client-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
    text-align: justify;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .adv-ref-link {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .adv-ref-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  /* ── ENGAGEMENT MODELS ── */
  .adv-models-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .adv-model {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: #ffffff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
  }

  .adv-model-label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-accent);
    background: var(--color-bg-accent);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .adv-model p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
    text-align: justify;
  }

  .adv-model-note {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── SCOPE LIST ── */
  .adv-scope-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .adv-scope-list li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    padding: 1rem 1.125rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-surface);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border-default);
    border-radius: 0 0.25rem 0.25rem 0;
    text-align: justify;
  }

  .adv-scope-list li strong {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ── WHAT WE DON'T DO ── */
  .adv-dont-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .adv-dont-list li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    padding: 1rem 1.125rem;
    background: #ffffff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    text-align: justify;
  }

  .adv-dont-list li strong {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* ── CTA ── */
  .adv-cta-section {
    background: var(--color-text-primary);
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }

  .adv-cta-inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .adv-cta-heading {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-cta-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
  }

  .adv-cta-sub {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #94a3b8;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 44ch;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .adv-cta-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .adv-btn-primary {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.625rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-cta-bg);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--color-cta-border);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-cta-text);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .adv-btn-primary:hover {
    background: #1e293b;
    border-color: #f59e0b;
  }

  .adv-btn-outline {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.625rem 1.25rem;
    border: 1.5px solid #475569;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-cta-text);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .adv-btn-outline:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-cta-border);
  }

  /* ── RESPONSIVE ── */
  @media (max-width: 52rem) {
    .adv-client-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .adv-models-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .adv-cta-inner {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }
</style>
